            "content": "{\n  \"buggy_files\": [\n    \"drivers/net/wireless/intel/iwlwifi/pcie/drv.c\"\n  ],\n  \"buggy_functions\": [\n    \"iwl_dev_info_table\"\n  ],\n  \"confidence\": 0.95,\n  \"reasoning\": \"The Intel iwlwifi 9260 device (0x2526) is missing PCI subdevice entries in the iwl_dev_info_table. Specifically, subdevice IDs 0x4010, 0x4014, 0x4018, and 0x401C are not mapped in the device info table. These entries should map to iwl9260_2ac_160_cfg configuration (similar to the existing 0x0010, 0x0014, 0x0018, 0x001C entries). Without these entries in iwl_dev_info_table, devices with these subdevice IDs fall back to a generic iwl9000_trans_cfg configuration, causing firmware loading failures. The bug report references missing entries for IDs 0x04010 (interpreted as 0x4010), 0x4018, and 0x401C, which are absent from both the iwl_dev_info_table and the pci_device_id_list tables in drv.c.\"\n}\n",
